               <p>HENRY MUNN, JUN. On the 30th of June, between ten and eleven o'clock in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18260914-445-crimeloc2507">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-445-crimeloc2507" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-445-crimeloc2507" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-445-off2505 t18260914-445-crimeloc2507"></join>, and felt my handkerchief taken from my pocket; I turned on my right, and saw two lads - the prisoner and Ash passed me on the left; I afterwards saw my handkerchief in the officer's possession.</p>


               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-445-person2302">
                  DANIEL 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18260914-445-person2302" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-445-person2302" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-445-person2302" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner near the Boltin-Tun, and followed him an another to St. Dunstan's church, where they turned round and followed Mr. Munn for some distance - as soon as they passed him I saw a handkerchief in the prisoner's left hand; I ran and tapped Mr. Munn on the shoulder - he said he had lost a handkerchief - I ran and took the prisoner with it, and then took the other, after some resistance.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating, that he had found the handkerchief on the pavement, and that the prosecutor had stated at Guildhall that he might possibly have dropped it.</p>
               <p>Mr. MUNN. I did not say so - I felt it taken from my pocket, turned round, and saw the prisoner pass me, but did not see it in his hand.</p>
               <p>Two witnesses gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18260914-445-verdict2508" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18260914-445-verdict2508" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>
